-Go to vcenter
-Create a new virtual machine on your host. 
-creation type -> create a new VM -> Click on next.
-Select a name and folder and Click on next
- Select a compute resource and Click on next
-Select datastore and Click on next.
-Select esxi 7 and Click on next.
-Guest OS Select os because it is open source.
-Upload iso file of OS.
-Select data store.
-Connect at power on . and click on next. click on finish
- Right Click on The Virtual Machine that is Just Created.
-Give name it a name and select host and then Click next.
-Select VMFS.
-Select customize the os and power on the virtual machine and Click on next. Click on Finish
-Here we created clone of our virtual machine.
-In policies and profiles ->VM Customization Specfications.
-Name it and Select Linux and Click on next.
-Fill the Required credentials.
-Select use the virtual machine 
-Give it a password
-Select Mumbai time zone.
-In network select use Standard network Settings and click on Finish
-VM customization and specification Done.
-Right Click on Virtual Machine and Click on Deploy from template and name it and Click on next. 
-Select Your Host.
-Select Your Storage and Click on Next.
-Select Customize the os and Select Power on the virtual machine after creation. 
-Click On Next and click finish
-we created rom template.
